Mpho Raborife, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg -&nbsp;A KwaZulu-Natal chief has been shot and killed in front of his daughter during a drive-by shooting on Monday evening, police said.Chief Linda Mathonsi, 58, was shot in the head and neck on Monday evening around 18:00 while travelling with his daughter, 25, who was also shot on the arm, Colonel Thembeka Mbele said.The two had been travelling in the Chappies area of Sundumbili when a car drove up next to theirs and an occupant began shooting at the two, she said.Mathonsi died on the scene and his daughter was taken to a nearby hospital for treatment.According to IPSS paramedics spokesperson Paul Herbst, the incident &ndash; which some have described as an assassination attempt &ndash; took place shortly after Mathonsi picked his daughter up near a library in the area. Police have opened a case of murder and attempted murder. The motive was still unknown, Mbele said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.